06:54.195 --> 07:00.441
and those, came down to see me and We would like for 
the city to

07:00.961 --> 07:18.385
give us, and I may be wrong about the number, it was a 
sizable number, out of some funds we had, a grant in

07:00.961 --> 07:18.385
effect to cover the shortage. And I thought about 
it. for a while and then in the end I talked to the

07:23.000 --> 07:31.808
council about it and they weren't too interested 
because legally we couldn't do it. And she was

07:33.750 --> 07:45.621
pretty upset about it, but at the time I told her, I 
said, you know Diana,

07:33.750 --> 07:45.621
do you have a list of your ex-students? She said no. 
I said do you ever ask them for money? No. I said, you

07:55.062 --> 08:04.262
know I think it's a little bit improper to come to 
ask the citizens of this city when you're not even

07:55.062 --> 08:04.262
asking your own graduates for money. Now, as far as 
I know, that is a unique reality for A&M. These

