09:34.360 --> 09:42.829
you were, when you graduated, you feel reasonably 
well prepared to be a real engineer? I thought I

09:42.910 --> 09:44.434
could lick the world. And you stayed on to do a 
graduate degree. Why? I thought that I really

09:51.632 --> 09:59.552
wanted to get a little more specialization. The 
electrical engineering department in those days

10:00.292 --> 10:13.388
gave you a pretty broad background, both power and 
electronics, as they called it. At the time I

10:16.031 --> 10:25.202
graduated the first time, I was prepared to go to 
GE, which I, by the way, did when I graduated. and

10:26.077 --> 10:28.981
reported to building one steam turbine. But I knew 
from day one I didn't want to be a power engineer.

10:33.348 --> 10:35.271
But my dad wanted me to do that. And I was only there 
three months until I had to report to the Air Force.

10:39.938 --> 10:40.839
And I never went back.

10:44.164 --> 10:48.190
So I decided the best thing I'd do is get a master's 
degree. You did a thesis and you did a project in

10:48.210 --> 10:53.097
those days.

