finished that master's degree, were you planning

10:56.947 --> 11:03.378
on being a self-employed engineer? You know, the 
day I finished there, I wasn't sure exactly what I

11:04.459 --> 11:13.273
wanted to do. I just knew that I

11:13.333 --> 11:20.485
was going to be self-employed. I didn't think I was 
going to be working for somebody. We've

11:24.667 --> 11:29.675
already asked this in a different way. What 
creates Aggie spirit, and why are Aggies so loyal?

11:35.264 --> 11:48.244
Well, I think it's the way they are indoctrinated,

11:35.264 --> 11:48.244
the way they relate

11:35.264 --> 11:48.244
to each other for the four or five years they're 
there. the the system the program at a m everything

11:50.013 --> 12:11.076
you do builds loyalty comradeship integrity hard 
work i think it's those things all put together If

12:11.512 --> 12:22.108
you were to go to City College in New York, right, 
you would not see your classmates except in class,

12:11.512 --> 12:22.108
and then you'd go home and you'd never see them 
again. You could go to the University of Texas.

12:26.574 --> 12:38.312
