All right, if you were the consultant, selected to 
come in and advise the A&M decision makers today

13:20.345 --> 13:32.060
about what they should do more of or less of in the 
future to keep A&M moving forward. What advice

13:32.120 --> 13:34.123
would you give them? Well, I think A&M is faced 
with, you know, several problems. I think they've

13:38.689 --> 13:42.994
done, in my opinion, almost everything right. I 
think their political skills are abysmal and I

13:42.974 --> 14:04.041
don't think you can live in this world and relate to 
Austin and Washington because unfortunately

13:42.974 --> 14:04.041
more and more of your success or failure depends on 
and I think we've got to do a better job relating

13:42.974 --> 14:04.041
with the political structure. You can't sit in 
College Station and say they can't touch me and I'm

14:04.201 --> 14:09.608
not going to worry about them. That's true. I think 
the university, and this is damned if they do,

14:12.303 --> 14:26.262
damned if they don't,

14:12.303 --> 14:26.262
the university is going to have to recognize the 
Hispanic population in the state.

14:30.668 --> 14:40.842
When you look at the population, and I think A&M has 
been, because it is so homogeneous, They've been

14:42.340 --> 14:45.886
able to set goals and stick with them. That's been 
the positive side. Whereas if you have this

14:47.608 --> 14:57.264
diverse population, you have too many different

14:47.608 --> 14:57.264
